course_name: Complete Agentic AI Bootcamp With LangGraph and Langchain
content:
I took this course to get a structured, end-to-end introduction to building agentic AI systems with LangGraph and LangChain, and it does a good job covering both the concepts and the practical implementation. It starts from the fundamentals of agentic AI and gradually moves into building real workflows, single-agent and multi-agent systems, memory, tools, and RAG-style applications. The course is long and detailed, and if you follow along, you come away with a solid understanding of how these frameworks are actually used in practice.

The main tradeoff is that the pacing can sometimes feel slow or repetitive, and some sections go deeper into setup or code mechanics than strictly necessary, while a few advanced topics (like deployment or more production-level patterns) could be expanded further. That said, for developers who want a thorough, step-by-step path into LangGraph-based agent systems and don‚Äôt mind a very detailed, classroom-style approach, this is a strong and useful course.

course_name: Complete Agentic AI Bootcamp With LangGraph and Langchain
Complete Agentic AI Bootcamp With LangGraph and Langchain
content:
Krish has put in a tremendous amount of effort in designing the curriculum and explaining the topics step by step. The course is well-structured and easy to follow, which makes learning enjoyable. I really appreciate the clarity and logical flow throughout the sessions.
That said, there are a few areas where improvements could make this course even better:

At some instances, more practical and relatable examples could have been used to strengthen understanding.
The final projects could have emphasized advanced concepts like memory chains, retrievers, and other tools‚Äîperhaps building a full-fledged chatbot as a capstone project.
In certain sections, Krish seemed to run through the code quickly; a bit more in-depth explanation of the underlying logic would have added great value.

Overall, it‚Äôs a very good course and I learned a lot. Thank you, Krish, for your hard work and dedication!

content:
I recently completed this course and overall, I had a positive experience. The content was comprehensive and well-organized, covering all the key aspects of the topic. The subjects were engaging and relevant, which kept my interest throughout the lessons.
The instructor appeared to be knowledgeable and competent, clearly explaining even the more complex concepts. However, I encountered a significant issue with the instructor‚Äôs keyboard usage‚Äîthere were numerous typos that were not corrected, which unfortunately made some parts of the course difficult to follow and slightly frustrating.
Despite this drawback, I believe the course offers solid educational value, and I would recommend it to others interested in the topic. I hope future updates will improve the quality of the written material.

course_name: Complete Agentic AI Bootcamp With LangGraph and Langchain
content:
Alright, so if you are looking to learn about Agentic AI and the different frameworks you need then this course is just the perfect course for you. Moreover, this course offers other important contents on python and generative AI as well. 

The one and only con I find in Krish Naik's courses are that he uses paid LLMs which is kind of hard for us (students) to get access to. I mean there is not a single doubt on the fact that he offers absolutely flawless references and stuff, in fact he also uses free LLM provider like Ollama often but using OpenAI becomes a bit problematic for us to cope with. Rest assured his courses are just way too perfect for you to gather knowledge.
Go for it!!
